Description: Small originally round clay disc with some parts of the edge broken off. The brown Nile clay has inclusions of mica and small pieces of charcoal and white accretions at the surface. One side is slightly convex and very smooth as if from an impression, the opposite side is slightly uneven but flat with voids of organic material like chaff.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14, north-west corner of street parallel with east wall of town, upper level.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 142)
